Citation.sTitle: Densities, Viscosities, and Conductivities of Phosphonic Acid Solutions in N,N-Dimethylformamide and Water
Citation.sAbstract: The viscosities, specific conductivities and densities of phosphonic acid solutions in N,Ndimethylformamide and water have been measured at temperatures from 298.15 to 338.15 K over the whole possible concentration range. Dependences of these properties on the mixture composition have been discussed and compared with the data for phosphoric acid solutions in the same solvents.
